1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:06,560
We're Exceeds... The only creatures in 
Edolas who have magic power inside them...

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:11,070
The reason we couldn't use magic was 
because of the unease in our hearts!

3
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:20,500
Let's go! We have to save everyone!

4
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,610
Aye!

5
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,800
Just as the legend says,

6
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:05,140
we knew that wizards from Earthland 
have magic power inside their bodies.

7
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:09,230
Just like the Exceeds...

8
00:02:09,490 --> 00:02:14,180
But that magic power cannot 
be compared to the Exceeds...

9
00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:20,970
So that girl named Lucy also 
has magic power in her body?

10
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:22,280
Yesh...

11
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:25,300
Then killing her is, whoa, such a waste!

12
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,970
Irrelevant!

13
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:33,840
We have orders to eliminate her 
from Queen Chagot of the Exceeds.

14
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,260
An order from the Queen?

15
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:43,110
We cannot oppose the Exceeds...

16
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:46,630
But, whoa, it's such a waste! Dang, man!

17
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:54,110
Furthermore, it is still impossible with our 
technology to extract magic power from human bodies.

18
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:58,150
Then, what will we do with 
those two Dragon Slayers?

19
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:03,370
Those are human, and yet not human.

20
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:06,050
If the experiment is a success,

21
00:03:06,050 --> 00:03:09,410
we could get our hands on a 
near-infinite supply of magic power.

22
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:11,800
Whoa!

23
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,290
Whoa, indeed!

24
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:17,480
Excellent, Byro. Begin immediately.

25
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,290
Yes, Your Highness.

26
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:25,240
And just in case, speed up the magic power 
extraction from the Earthland lacrima.

27
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,560
Understood.

28
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:32,470
In just a bit, this world 
might get magic power back!

29
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,920
Whoa!

30
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,020
It'll be a great thing.

31
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:39,370
What'll you do first, Sugar Boy?

32
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,740
Maybe, Magic Surfing?

33
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:44,740
I wanna surf, too!

34
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,240
What is the matter, Panther Lily?

35
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:52,370
Your Highness, it is about the 
recent military buildup...

36
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:59,620
Never mind.  If you'll excuse me...

37
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,680
Code ETD.

38
00:04:21,890 --> 00:04:26,440
Happy and Carla are a race called the Exceed.

39
00:04:27,710 --> 00:04:32,600
Exceed... On this world, they're like angels.

40
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:35,620
And their Queen Chagot is God.

41
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:40,580
The word of God is law, and it 
is her job to regulate humanity.

42
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:47,720
If her mouth says "die", that 
human has no choice but to die.

43
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:52,210
This is ridiculous! How 
unfair of a law can you get?

44
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,430
You've researched this 
world quite well, I see.

45
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:07,960
Erza!

46
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:10,450
Is everyone safe?

47
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,910
Yes, everyone is safe.

48
00:05:13,490 --> 00:05:15,040
Thank goodness.

49
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,350
I'm impressed you can still 
put on such a brave face.

50
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:21,250
You do understand the 
position you are in, yes?

51
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:23,650
Yeah. I guess you're right.

52
00:05:25,620 --> 00:05:28,220
Your face, your voice...

53
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:32,690
They're just like the Erza I know, so I 
couldn't help but feel a little at ease...

54
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:36,310
The Earthland me?

55
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:41,270
In our world, you're a member of Fairy Tail!

56
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,400
What?

57
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:47,040
You're strong, and cool... 
and a little bit scary.

58
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,670
But everyone really depends on you.

59
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:56,360
You also love sweets and cute clothes, 
and are actually quite girly!

60
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,430
And you...

61
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:03,130
No more talking.

62
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:07,840
Sorry, but I'm not the Erza you know.

63
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:15,500
Please, help me!

64
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,930
I just want to save my friends, that's all!

65
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:24,730
You might be a different person, that's 
true. But I can tell you're the same deep down!

66
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:29,280
You aren't a person that can 
laugh at people's suffering!

67
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,120
Silence!

68
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:37,790
Wait a sec...

69
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:40,400
You will die here.

70
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:43,540
Erza would never do this to 
someone who wasn't resisting!

71
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,840
Erza is kind!

72
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,670
She could never do this, no way!

73
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:51,110
What a simpleton!

74
00:06:51,110 --> 00:06:54,550
People's suffering is <i>my</i> favorite dish!

75
00:06:55,950 --> 00:07:01,810
You realize why I'm called the Fairy Hunter? 
I've killed countless members of Fairy Tail.

76
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:10,450
How dare you say those things in 
Erza's voice, with Erza's face!

77
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:14,300
Goodbye, Lucy.

78
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,440
Lucy!

79
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:26,710
Happy, Carla!

80
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:29,510
Exceeds?

81
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:33,300
Everything'll be okay! 
We're here to save you!

82
00:07:38,790 --> 00:07:39,880
Thank you!

83
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:42,550
Huh? Your wings are back?

84
00:07:42,550 --> 00:07:44,810
Seems like it was a problem with our hearts.

85
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:49,360
It's been so long, I misjudged and 
gave it too much of a boost...

86
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:53,120
What is the meaning of this?

87
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:57,450
This individual was ordered 
to be eliminated by the Queen!

88
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:59,760
The order has been rescinded.

89
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:03,530
But even if it comes directly from an Exceed,

90
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:06,980
you shouldn't have the authority 
to reverse an order from the Queen!

91
00:08:09,380 --> 00:08:12,260
Please hand that woman over to me.

92
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:15,350
Human, know your place.

93
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:18,330
Learn who stands before you.

94
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:26,030
It is I, Princess Carla, 
daughter of Queen Chagot!

95
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:32,190
I sincerely apologize!

96
00:08:34,540 --> 00:08:38,300
Where is Wen- are the two Dragon Slayers?

97
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,200
The basement of the west tower.

98
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:42,290
Release them at once.

99
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:46,520
I do not have the authority to do that.

100
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,350
I don't care, just do it!

101
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:50,640
Yes! But...

102
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:53,970
Erza, those two Exceeds are Fallen!

103
00:08:53,970 --> 00:08:56,630
They've been chased out of Extalia!

104
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:59,840
Who's that? An ally of yours?

105
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,390
Doesn't look like it!

106
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:04,590
There weren't any Exceeds 
that were all buff like that!

107
00:09:04,590 --> 00:09:05,530
We're running away.

108
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:07,850
Wait, weren't you a princess?

109
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:16,100
How dare they?!

110
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,840
Alert all the troops!

111
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:20,140
Two Fallen have escaped with a prisoner!

112
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:22,510
The Fallen Exceeds are blue and white!

113
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,410
Eliminate them on sight!

114
00:09:25,890 --> 00:09:27,750
Thanks, you two.

115
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,990
You're not angry?

116
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,210
About what?

117
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,360
It's our fault that you were caught.

118
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:39,400
But then you went and saved me.

119
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:41,150
Right, Happy?

120
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:43,100
Sorry, Lucy...

121
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:46,930
I'm telling you, I'm not angry one bit!

122
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:51,740
Anyway, I'm shocked to hear you're 
the daughter of the Queen?

123
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:53,740
I didn't know that either.

124
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,980
It was just a bluff, obviously.

125
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,320
Why're you making that face, Happy?

126
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:05,080
Oh, I just thought, "That's 
the Carla I know."

127
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:08,580
Huh? Did she just call him Happy?

128
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:13,620
Be quiet, you. Right now, we 
have to hurry and find Wendy.

129
00:10:11,710 --> 00:10:13,330
I see!

130
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:14,560
Where?

131
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:15,780
The west tower.

132
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:18,980
She said the two were being 
held in the basement.

133
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:21,200
What are you smiling about, Lucy?

134
00:10:22,340 --> 00:10:23,970
Nothing much.

135
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:27,190
Isn't that the west tower?

136
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,520
What is that sound?

137
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:36,190
We've found you, Fallen!

138
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,740
It's a flock of cats!

139
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:40,150
Go!

140
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:41,950
Men!

141
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:44,350
It's dangerous in the air!

142
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:46,180
Let's land on solid ground!

143
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,750
Wait, Carla!

144
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,210
There's enemies on the ground, too!

145
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,850
Lucy, what about your Celestial Magic?

146
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:58,710
This sticky stuff seems to block my magic!

147
00:11:00,180 --> 00:11:02,680
What is the meaning of this?

148
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:07,350
The Extalia Royal Guard has 
come chasing after two Fallen!

149
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:21,730
Activate Code ETD!

150
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,080
Code ETD!

151
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,660
Now?!

152
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:37,540
Number 10-12, set!

153
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:40,480
14 and 15, all set!

154
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,880
6-9, okay!

155
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:48,220
He activated the Territorial Security
 Last Defense Operation?

156
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:50,470
We'll head inside a building!

157
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:52,580
Code ETD!

158
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:54,090
Activate!

159
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:21,710
What devilry is this, humans?!

160
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:24,050
Why are they aiming at the Exceed?

161
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,970
What does it mean?

162
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:31,210
Exceeds are like angels 
or gods to humans, right?

163
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:33,480
Is this... a rebellion?

164
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:39,010
I don't really know, but it seems like our 
best course of action is to use the confusion.

165
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:41,970
We'll go save Wendy and Natsu 
while we have the chance!

166
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:42,990
Aye!

167
00:12:43,610 --> 00:12:46,730
Damn! The Fallen and the prisoner have...

168
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:48,670
They should be heading toward the west tower!

169
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,910
Double up the defenses!

170
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:51,660
Yes, ma'am!

171
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:57,440
How dare you, humans!

172
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:02,380
The Queen will not stay silent on this! Men!

173
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:18,000
The Exceeds turned into a lacrima!

174
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,020
We've really done it now...

175
00:13:20,020 --> 00:13:21,550
Will it be okay?

176
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:24,990
There are no gods in this world!

177
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:30,400
Only we humans suffer 
from limited magic power!

178
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:34,620
All the while, the Exceed revel 
in their infinite magic power!

179
00:13:35,050 --> 00:13:36,120
Why?

180
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:43,530
Why can we not obtain that 
infinity so near to us?

181
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:48,380
I proclaim the end to the 
era where we are controlled!

182
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:51,830
Everything is for the future of humanity!

183
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:55,240
For creating a prosperous magic society!

184
00:13:55,240 --> 00:14:00,130
My soldiers, stand with me!

185
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:05,690
Code ETD: Exceed Total Destruction!

186
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:10,160
Activate operation Extermination of Angels!

187
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:19,730
Whoa, things just got real.

188
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:22,750
Perhaps it was inevitable.

189
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:29,340
So this is why he was 
building up the military?

190
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:38,960
If we can steal the Exceeds' magic power, 
our kingdom can obtain an infinite supply.

191
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:42,250
Your Highness, the Queen is coming to attack!

192
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:45,520
The military might of Extalia is incredible!

193
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:50,080
I captured the Dragon Slayers 
precisely for this time.

194
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,650
Now is the time we must cast down the gods.

195
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:55,470
Hurry and extract their Dragon Slayer Magic.

196
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:56,370
Byro!

197
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:07,980
Are you two prepared for this?

198
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,900
Things have really gotten crazy, it seems.

199
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:19,900
I can't believe that the humans and 
the Exceeds have started a war!

200
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:22,600
It doesn't have anything to do with us.

201
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:26,740
They're both the same! They can 
fight all they want, I don't care.

202
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:44,140
You won't be going any further.

203
00:15:44,140 --> 00:15:48,420
For goodness sake! Weren't you 
going to leave us alone for now?

204
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:05,780
You took a direct hit from my magic.

205
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:07,650
And yet you're still alive?

206
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:10,630
But this will be your end.

207
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:18,540
I never received an order 
to capture you alive.

208
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:21,020
I'll strike the final blow!

209
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:38,520
Happy, wake up!

210
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:43,710
Natsu, I'm sorry... I was so 
close to saving you, but...

211
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:47,160
It looks like this is as far as I get.

212
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:53,130
Huh? That's me. And Natsu is there, too.

213
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:59,430
That's right... Natsu would 
never give up, no matter what.

214
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:25,710
Damn it!

215
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:32,110
Dragon Slayers are impressive, indeed... 
Both of you have considerable magic power.

216
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:38,930
Natsu-san, are you okay?

217
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:44,410
Yeah. And don't you dare give up on me!

218
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,930
We'll get out of this, for sure!

219
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:50,910
Don't give up hope!

220
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:51,830
Right!

221
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:55,270
I'm sure our friends will come for us, right?

222
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:01,830
Both of you don't know when to quit, do you?

223
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:05,870
Is that part of the toughness 
of being a Dragon Slayer?

224
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:07,940
Natsu-san!

225
00:18:11,780 --> 00:18:12,920
Wendy!

226
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:17,530
Don't... Don't you ever give up!

227
00:18:18,150 --> 00:18:19,110
Natsu-san!

228
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:22,260
Next up it'll be your turn!

229
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:27,120
Stop it! I'll give you my 
magic power in Wendy's place!

230
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:29,780
Hey, are they here?

231
00:18:29,780 --> 00:18:33,330
No, not here. Where did they go?

232
00:18:34,170 --> 00:18:37,590
We're basically completely trapped here.

233
00:18:37,590 --> 00:18:41,570
There's probably a very tight 
guard around Wendy and Natsu.

234
00:18:41,570 --> 00:18:43,670
Even if we wanted to, we couldn't get close.

235
00:18:44,050 --> 00:18:45,760
Even though we made it this far...

236
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:47,660
Wendy...

237
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:53,940
Happy!

238
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,010
You can't give up!

239
00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:02,860
Natsu never gave up, no matter what happened!

240
00:19:03,450 --> 00:19:07,870
He's made it this far by always 
fighting through to the end!

241
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:13,000
And now it's our turn to learn from Natsu!

242
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:15,230
Do you have some kind of plan?

243
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:28,890
Screw this!

244
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,760
He's here!

245
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,550
It's the blue Exceed!

246
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:40,490
Take my Poison Mist attack!

247
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,320
Don't inhale it!

248
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,370
Don't be afraid! It's just flour!

249
00:19:50,430 --> 00:19:51,590
Crap!

250
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:52,780
Don't let him get away!

251
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,940
Looks like that worked.

252
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:56,570
Yeah.

253
00:19:59,230 --> 00:20:01,630
Happy, you'd better escape!

254
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:13,670
Have one sacrifice himself, and rescue 
them when the guard is weakened...

255
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:16,900
I figured you would try something like that.

256
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,570
Wendy!

257
00:20:23,590 --> 00:20:24,500
Wendy!

258
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:27,800
What the hell are you 
doing to Natsu and Wendy?

259
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:33,430
We're stealing the magic power 
we need for Code ETD from them.

260
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,920
Stop it!

261
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,130
Stop it!

262
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:43,560
Stop this at once!

263
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:45,870
We caught him.

264
00:20:48,130 --> 00:20:48,970
Happy!

265
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:56,430
Your devil's luck just ran out.

266
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:02,150
Give Wendy back!

267
00:21:12,540 --> 00:21:16,250
I won't let you lay a hand on Carla!

268
00:21:16,850 --> 00:21:18,430
I won't let you!

269
00:21:18,430 --> 00:21:19,840
Happy!

270
00:21:27,170 --> 00:21:29,120
Fine then. I'll start with you.

271
00:21:29,550 --> 00:21:31,390
No!!

272
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,980
What now?

273
00:21:43,850 --> 00:21:46,100
Hey, you there.

274
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:51,080
You did this knowing they're 
members of our guild?

275
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:57,830
We will never forgive those who lay 
hands on our fellow guild members!

276
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,710
But, how did you...

277
00:22:00,710 --> 00:22:05,790
All of you are now our enemies!

278
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,470
Enemies of Fairy Tail!

279
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,520
Gray! Erza!

280
00:23:55,770 --> 00:23:58,690
Hey, hey, hey... What the heck's goin' on?

281
00:23:58,690 --> 00:24:00,440
Why're you so shaken up?

282
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:03,530
There are two Erzas, and what's 
more, they're fighting each other!

283
00:24:03,530 --> 00:24:05,840
Oh, that's right. You didn't know, Natsu.

284
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,910
Actually, that lacrima...

285
00:24:08,450 --> 00:24:10,460
It's the end of this world!

286
00:24:10,460 --> 00:24:13,860
Do you think he'll listen to a thing I say?

287
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,970
Next time: Erza vs. Erza!

288
00:24:16,970 --> 00:24:18,890
You're always like this, Natsu.

289
00:24:18,890 --> 00:24:20,140
Just before, you were...

290
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:21,800
Being shaken up sure works up an appetite!

291
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,600
Listen to me!!

